      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why would a formerly successful stock suddenly plummet from $50 down to $5?</summary>
        <p>This catastrophic drop could happen due to a severe, underlying business failure, massive accounting fraud, or the loss of a key patent. However, it could also simply be the completely harmless mathematical result of a 10-for-1 forward stock split. In a stock split, the company intentionally issues significantly more shares to the public while perfectly proportionally reducing the price of each share, leaving the absolute total value of your investment completely unchanged.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Where is the absolute safest place to search for and buy stocks trading under $10?</summary>
        <p>The absolutely safest place to hunt for these equities is exclusively on major, heavily regulated national exchanges like the NYSE (New York Stock Exchange) or the NASDAQ. You must absolutely avoid Over-The-Counter (OTC) markets or the completely unregulated 'Pink Sheets,' which completely lack strict, audited financial reporting requirements and are notoriously prone to massive pump-and-dump scams and dangerously low liquidity.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
